    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Implement force_RRC_IDLE() telnet command for nrUE\n\n### Summary\nThe `force_RRC_IDLE()` function was referenced in documentation and testing procedures but was not actually implemented in the telnet server interface for nrUE. This caused issues when trying to force UEs into RRC IDLE state during testing scenarios.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_ciUE.c`: Added the missing `force_RRC_IDLE()` function implementation and registered it as a telnet command\n- Added necessary include headers for RRC functionality\n- Implemented proper parameter validation and error handling\n- Used existing `nr_rrc_going_to_IDLE()` function for proper state transition\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, when attempting to use the `force_RRC_IDLE` command through telnet interface:\n```\ntelnet localhost 9090\n> force_RRC_IDLE\n```\n\nThe command would fail with \"command not found\" error. After this fix, the command properly executes and forces the UE into RRC IDLE state, with appropriate confirmation message returned through the telnet interface.\n\nThe function now properly transitions the UE RRC state from CONNECTED/INACTIVE to IDLE by calling the existing RRC state management functions, stopping appropriate timers, releasing radio resources, and notifying upper layers of the connection release.\n"
}